column4: Trial identifier used by lead organization, ie. Center for Experimental Therapeutics Program (CTEP) ID or Industry Sponsored ID.  This is usually a short identifier. Example: E4412.
Batch identification number. Unique to every batch.
Indicates what site is filling out the assay.
Path to file, relative to the intake bucket.
Specimen identifier assigned by the CIMAC-CIDC Network. Formatted as CTTTPPPSS.AA for trial code TTT, participant PPP, sample SS, and aliquot AA.
Identifier of a region of interest within one mIF slide, e.g. 1, 2, 3 or [123x321]
A text description of this ROI. Eg: decidua
A text comment regarding this slide.
the ID as listed in channel_names files and used in the OME tiffs
Antibody type collected for this study.
the antibody's Research Resource Identifier from SciCrunch
the UniProt accession number of the target protein
Identification number assigned to the particular quantity or lot of material from manufacturer.
the final working dilution of the stock antibody
the numeric value of the antibody concentration
the units of the concentration value
Antibody registry catalog number assigned to antibody sample.
the tag to which the antibody is conjugated and used for detection
